	<h2>Sailing Charters</h2>
	<p>
		What better way to enjoy Channel Islands National Park than from
		the deck of your own private yacht? The Santa Barbara Channel,
		which runs between mainland California and Santa Cruz Island,
		offers pristine sunsets, affable wildlife, and beautiful coastline.
		Interestingly, this area is home to the greatest diversity of
		cetaceans (whales and dolphins) than any other place on earth.
		Sea lions and dozens of species of sea birds are also regular
		visitors. The Channel Islands Center for Leadership and Team
		Building can help you explore these sights on your very own vessel
		with friends, family, or coworkers.
	</p>
